6. IMPORTANT CURRENT ISSUE: CONTROLS HIDDEN BEFORE UPLOAD

The editor controls currently do not show until after an image is uploaded.

This is wrong.

The editor controls should always be visible immediately when the editor opens, even before an image is uploaded.

Before upload, users should be able to set:
- Watermark Text
- Font Family
- Font Size
- Text Color
- Opacity
- Rotation
- Placement

The preview area can still show an upload placeholder.

When the user uploads an image, all settings chosen before upload should apply immediately to the watermark.

The app should not force users to upload an image before they can customize their watermark settings.

====================================================

7. IMPORTANT CURRENT ISSUE: EDITOR RETURNS TO LANDING PAGE

The app appears to send the user back to the landing page after a short time, preview reload, refresh, inactivity, or testing delay.

This is wrong.

Do not call this logging out because there is no login system yet.

The editor should not automatically return to the landing page every 30 seconds, every minute, every few minutes, or after inactivity.

If the user is in the editor, the app should keep them in the editor.

At minimum:
- Store the current view in localStorage.
- If the last view was editor, reload back into the editor.
- If the last view was landing, reload back into the landing page.
- Back to Home should intentionally set the view to landing.
- Start Watermarking should intentionally set the view to editor.
- Start Free should intentionally set the view to editor.

Do not reset the editor view unless the user intentionally clicks Back to Home.

