9. IMAGE UPLOAD RULES

Upload should support:
- PNG
- JPG
- JPEG
- WebP

Upload should include:
- regular file picker
- drag-and-drop upload
- replace image option

Images must stay local in the browser.

Do not upload images to a server.

Do not add cloud storage.

Use safe browser preview behavior such as URL.createObjectURL.

Clean up object URLs when:
- image changes
- image resets
- component unmounts

Use a reasonable file size limit such as 15MB unless changed later.

Show helpful error messages for:
- unsupported file type
- failed image loading
- file too large

The uploaded image should:
- preserve aspect ratio
- never stretch
- never distort
- fit inside the preview area
- avoid cropping unless the user chooses cropping later

